@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>@ViewData["Title"]</title>

    <!-- Custome CSS -->
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f8fafc;
            color: #333;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        .container {
            width: 80%;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 30px 0;
        }

        header {
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 40px;
        }

            header h1 {
                font-size: 36px;
                color: #2d6a4f;
            }

        .section-title {
            font-size: 24px;
            color: #2d6a4f;
            margin-top: 30px;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        .section-content {
            font-size: 16px;
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: #555;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        .footer {
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 14px;
            color: #888;
            margin-top: 50px;
        }

            .footer a {
                color: #2d6a4f;
                text-decoration: none;
            }

                .footer a:hover {
                    text-decoration: underline;
                }


        /* Back to Top Button */
        .back-to-top {
            position: fixed;
            bottom: 20px;
            right: 20px;
            background-color: #2d6a4f;
            color: white;
            padding: 10px 15px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            text-decoration: none;
            font-size: 1rem;
        }

            .back-to-top:hover {
                color: white;
                background-color: darkseagreen;
            }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div class="container">
        <header>
            <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
        </header>

        <section>
            <div class="section-title">1. Information We Collect</div>
            <div class="section-content">
                <p>We only collect the essential information needed for the operation of our services:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Authentication Information:</strong> To secure your account, we collect your email address and a PIN for authentication purposes.</li>
                    <li><strong>Meal Plan Records:</strong> We generate and store meal plan records based on the information you provide (e.g., dietary preferences). These records help us tailor your meal plans and provide a personalized experience.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <div class="section-title">2. How We Use Your Information</div>
            <div class="section-content">
                <p>Your information is used exclusively for the following purposes:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Meal Plan Generation:</strong> The data you provide is used to generate personalized meal plans.</li>
                    <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> Your email and PIN are used to manage your account and secure access to your meal plans.</li>
                    <li><strong>Improvement of Services:</strong> We may use the data to improve our meal planning algorithms and enhance your user experience in the future.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <div class="section-title">3. Data Retention</div>
            <div class="section-content">
                <p>We retain your meal plan records and authentication details for the duration of your use of our app. You may delete your account and associated data at any time by contacting us.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <div class="section-title">4. How We Protect Your Information</div>
            <div class="section-content">
                <p>We implement industry-standard security measures to safeguard your personal information. All sensitive data is encrypted, and we use secure server technologies to protect your data.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <div class="section-title">5. Data Sharing</div>
            <div class="section-content">
                <p>We do not share, sell, or rent your personal information to third parties. Your data is used solely for the purpose of providing our services and improving the app's functionality.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <div class="section-title">6. Future Use of Data</div>
            <div class="section-content">
                <p>While we currently do not use any information for marketing or advertising, we may, in the future, use meal plan records for analysis and optimization of meal recommendations.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <div class="section-title">7. Your Rights</div>
            <div class="section-content">
                <p>You have the right to:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Access:</strong> You have the right to access the data we have collected about you.</li>
                    <li><strong>Correction:</strong> You can update or correct your personal information through your account settings.</li>
                    <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> You can request the deletion of your account and meal plan records at any time.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <div class="section-title">8. Changes to This Privacy Policy</div>
            <div class="section-content">
                <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any significant changes by posting the new policy on this page. Please review this page periodically for any updates.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

